commit.message: Update README.
Fix sync distance calculation for 14-bit streams.
Minor LBR decoder fixes.
Change spatial info decoding logic.
Shorten a table.
Reuse EXSS table for LBR sample rates.
Fix potential LBR parsing failure.
Simplify LFE sample sign conversion.
Switch LBR decoder to fast IMDCT implementation.

Replace floating point IDCT with generic implementation.

Based on the fast algorithm to compute DCT-IV given in "The transform
and data compression handbook", P.C. Yip, K.R. Rao.

Stop using IDCT defines for fixed point transform.

Prepare for the next commit that will remove these defines. Code looks
better without this cruft actually.

This partially reverts commits b35fdcf, bdcdf30.

Handle missing or reordered chunks in a safer way.

Also verify chunk dependencies: there is no point in decoding
timesamples chunks if high-res grid is missing, etc.
Ignore possible extra data after LBR frame chunk.

Minor simplification.

Number of subbands is always a multiple of 8.
Fix some quantized amplitude range checks.

Handle remaining tonal chunk types.

Untested.
Support embedded stereo downmix.
Limit maximum quantized amplitude to 56.
Make LBR output clipping optional.
Drop redundant memset.

Support LBR sample rates less than 48 kHz.

LFE interpolation still only works at 48 kHz, though.
Prevent possible LBR chunk overread.
Mark lbr_clear() as cold function.
Optimize scalefactor loop without second grid.
Sanitize quantized amplitude and phase.

Add initial LBR decoding support.

Currently limited to max. 5.1 decoding at 48 kHz.
Simplify condition.
Initialize number of decoded X96 channels to zero.
Reject invalid EXSS speaker layout mask.
Reject invalid core shift.
